---
const capabilities = [
  {
    title: "Use capable models on iPhone",
    body: "Install supported MLX models and use local inference for everyday work, private drafts, and context-heavy questions that should stay close.",
    meta: "Local chat, vision, embeddings",
  },
  {
    title: "Add cloud power only when you choose it",
    body: "Bring your own provider keys for harder tasks. Pines keeps cloud routing explicit and never turns a local request into a cloud request silently.",
    meta: "OpenAI-compatible, OpenRouter, Anthropic, Gemini",
  },
  {
    title: "Keep useful context in a private vault",
    body: "Import files and notes so Pines can retrieve the right material later instead of asking you to paste the same context again.",
    meta: "PDF, images, Markdown, JSON, CSV",
  },
];

const trustItems = [
  "API keys stay in Keychain.",
  "Normal inference remains local unless a cloud route is configured and chosen.",
  "Private vault and MCP resource context require per-turn approval before cloud use.",
  "Tool specs declare permissions, side effects, network policy, and timeout.",
  "CloudKit sync is optional and deliberately excludes secrets and model binaries.",
];
---

<section class="section capability-grid" aria-labelledby="capabilities-title">
  <div class="section-copy">
    <span class="section-kicker">Why Pines</span>
    <h2>Your phone can be more than a remote control for cloud chat.</h2>
    <p>
      Pines brings local models, optional cloud providers, private context, and tools into
      one iPhone workspace with an Apple Watch companion for quick access.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="capability-cards">
    {capabilities.map((item) => (
      <article>
        <span>{item.meta}</span>
        <h3>{item.title}</h3>
        <p>{item.body}</p>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section route-map" id="privacy">
  <div class="route-panel local-panel">
    <span class="section-kicker">Default Boundary</span>
    <h2>On device until you decide otherwise.</h2>
    <p>
      Pines is local-first by default. Chats, model state, vault documents, embeddings,
      attachments, and normal inference stay on device unless you configure a provider and choose a cloud route.
    </p>
    <div class="route-ladder" aria-label="Execution modes">
      <span>Local only</span>
      <span>Prefer local</span>
      <span>Cloud allowed</span>
      <span>Cloud required</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="route-panel trust-panel">
    <h3>Visible Consent Points</h3>
    <ul>
      {trustItems.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section mcp-section">
  <div class="mcp-terminal" aria-label="MCP capability preview">
    <div class="terminal-bar">
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
      <strong>MCP Streamable HTTP</strong>
    </div>
    <pre><code>tools/list        enabled per server
resources/read    selected by user
prompts/get       editable arguments
sampling/create   reviewed before return</code></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="section-copy">
    <span class="section-kicker">Tools And MCP</span>
    <h2>Connect useful systems while keeping actions legible.</h2>
    <p>
      MCP servers can bring tools, resources, prompts, subscriptions, and sampling into Pines.
      Network operations, private context, browser actions, and sampling results remain approval-aware.
    </p>
    <a class="text-link" href="https://github.com/RNT56/pines/blob/main/docs/MCP.md">Read the MCP notes</a>
  </div>
</section>
